Package: moodDispensery
Type: Package
Title: Sentiment-Based Mood Classification for Short Text Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Grace", "Whitehurst",
      email = "gwhitehurst@usf.edu",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: moodDispensery is an R package designed to analyze short text inputs 
    and classify their overall emotional tone, similar to a "mood ring" for data. 
    The package processes text-only input and returns structured sentiment insights, 
    including sentiment scores and mood labels. This tool is intended for introductory 
    exploration of natural language processing (NLP) concepts in data science and 
    machine learning. It is best suited for small-scale text data (approximately 
    50–100 words) and provides simple, interpretable outputs through functions such as 
    analyze_sentiment(), classify_mood(), and theme_summary().
Imports: dplyr, tidytext, tidyr
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
